Suppose we have a Riemannian manifold ${(M,g)}$, where ${g}$ is the metric of ${M}$. If ${f}$ ${\in}$ ${D(M)}$ (i.e. smooth function on ${M}$), and ${f}$ is positive. So, we can define a new metric ${g'}$ = ${fg}$ (i.e. for given any vector field ${X}$ and ${Y}$ on ${M}$, ${g'(X,Y)} = { f g(X,Y)}$. I already checked that the new connection $
abla'$ associated with ${g'}$, we have: ${
abla'}_X Y$ = ${
abla}_X Y + S(X,Y)$ where S(X,Y) = $(1/f)$ $[$ ${X(f)Y+(Yf)X-g(X,Y)\operatorname{grad}(f)}$ $]$ and $\operatorname{grad}(f)$ satisfies $X(f) = g(X,\operatorname{grad}(f))$ (Actually, it is an exercise in do Carmo "Riemannian Geometry" , so I just follow the Hint) Now, I am trying to comput new curvature tensor, sectional curvature, Ricci curvature and scalar curvature. For curvature tensor $R'$, My result is  $$  egin{eqnarray} R'(X,Y)Z &=& R(X,Y)Z + {
abla}_Y S(X,Y) - {
abla}_X S(Y,Z) \                                     &+& S(Y,S(X,Z))  - S(X,S(Y,Z)) \                                     &+& S(X,{
abla}_X Z) - S(X,{
abla}_Y Z)                                     + S([X,Y],Z) \end{eqnarray} $$ And I don't know how can I do in next step. How about sectional curvature, Ricci curvature and scalar curvature? Everybody who can give me some hint? Thanks !

